<!-- CZÄ˜ÅšÄ† 6: PRZYKÅADY ROZWIÄ„ZANE -->
<!-- ============================================ -->
<section class="section" id="s6">
    <div class="section-label">CzÄ™Å›Ä‡ 06</div>
    <h2>PrzykÅ‚ady rozwiÄ…zane krok po kroku</h2>

    <div class="example">
        <div class="example-header">
            <div class="icon">ğŸ”</div>
            PrzykÅ‚ad 7 â€” Wyznaczanie wyrazÃ³w ciÄ…gu
        </div>
        <p>Dany jest ciÄ…g <span class="im">a<sub>n</sub> = (âˆ’1)<sup>n</sup> Â· n</span>. Wyznacz pierwsze 6 wyrazÃ³w.</p>
        <div class="step">
            a<sub>1</sub> = (âˆ’1)Â¹ Â· 1 = <strong>âˆ’1</strong><br>
            a<sub>2</sub> = (âˆ’1)Â² Â· 2 = <strong>2</strong><br>
            a<sub>3</sub> = (âˆ’1)Â³ Â· 3 = <strong>âˆ’3</strong><br>
            a<sub>4</sub> = (âˆ’1)â´ Â· 4 = <strong>4</strong><br>
            a<sub>5</sub> = (âˆ’1)âµ Â· 5 = <strong>âˆ’5</strong><br>
            a<sub>6</sub> = (âˆ’1)â¶ Â· 6 = <strong>6</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="result">CiÄ…g: âˆ’1, 2, âˆ’3, 4, âˆ’5, 6, â€¦ â€” ciÄ…g naprzemienny (zmienia znaki). Jest niemonotoniczny!</div>
    </div>

    <div class="example">
        <div class="example-header">
            <div class="icon">ğŸ”</div>
            PrzykÅ‚ad 8 â€” MonotonicznoÅ›Ä‡ ciÄ…gu z uÅ‚amkiem
        </div>
        <p>Zbadaj monotonicznoÅ›Ä‡ ciÄ…gu <span class="im">a<sub>n</sub> = <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">2n + 1</span><span class="frac-den">n + 3</span></span></span></p>
        <div class="step">
            <strong>Krok 1:</strong> Obliczamy a<sub>n+1</sub><br>
            a<sub>n+1</sub> = (2(n+1) + 1) / ((n+1) + 3) = (2n + 3) / (n + 4)
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <strong>Krok 2:</strong> Obliczamy rÃ³Å¼nicÄ™ a<sub>n+1</sub> âˆ’ a<sub>n</sub><br>
            = <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">2n+3</span><span class="frac-den">n+4</span></span> âˆ’ <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">2n+1</span><span class="frac-den">n+3</span></span><br>
            Sprowadzamy do wspÃ³lnego mianownika:<br>
            = <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">(2n+3)(n+3) âˆ’ (2n+1)(n+4)</span><span class="frac-den">(n+4)(n+3)</span></span><br>
            <br>
            Licznik:<br>
            (2n+3)(n+3) = 2nÂ² + 6n + 3n + 9 = 2nÂ² + 9n + 9<br>
            (2n+1)(n+4) = 2nÂ² + 8n + n + 4 = 2nÂ² + 9n + 4<br>
            <br>
            RÃ³Å¼nica licznikÃ³w: (2nÂ² + 9n + 9) âˆ’ (2nÂ² + 9n + 4) = <strong>5</strong>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <strong>Krok 3:</strong> Zatem<br>
            a<sub>n+1</sub> âˆ’ a<sub>n</sub> = <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">5</span><span class="frac-den">(n+4)(n+3)</span></span><br>
            <br>
            Mianownik (n+4)(n+3) &gt; 0 dla kaÅ¼dego n âˆˆ â„•âº<br>
            Licznik = 5 &gt; 0<br>
            WiÄ™c caÅ‚a rÃ³Å¼nica jest <strong>zawsze dodatnia</strong>.
        </div>
        <div class="result">CiÄ…g (a<sub>n</sub>) jest rosnÄ…cy.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="example">
        <div class="example-header">
            <div class="icon">ğŸ”</div>
            PrzykÅ‚ad 9 â€” MonotonicznoÅ›Ä‡ ciÄ…gu z potÄ™gÄ…
        </div>
        <p>Zbadaj monotonicznoÅ›Ä‡ ciÄ…gu <span class="im">a<sub>n</sub> = <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">n</span><span class="frac-den">2<sup>n</sup></span></span></span></p>
        <div class="step">
            <strong>Krok 1:</strong> Wyrazy sÄ… dodatnie (n &gt; 0, 2<sup>n</sup> &gt; 0), wiÄ™c stosujemy metodÄ™ ilorazowÄ….
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <strong>Krok 2:</strong> Obliczamy iloraz<br>
            a<sub>n+1</sub>/a<sub>n</sub> = <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">(n+1)</span><span class="frac-den">2<sup>n+1</sup></span></span> : <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">n</span><span class="frac-den">2<sup>n</sup></span></span> = <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">(n+1)</span><span class="frac-den">2<sup>n+1</sup></span></span> Â· <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">2<sup>n</sup></span><span class="frac-den">n</span></span> = <strong><span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">n+1</span><span class="frac-den">2n</span></span></strong>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <strong>Krok 3:</strong> Badamy kiedy <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">n+1</span><span class="frac-den">2n</span></span> &lt; 1<br>
            <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">n+1</span><span class="frac-den">2n</span></span> &lt; 1<br>
            n + 1 &lt; 2n<br>
            1 &lt; n<br>
            Czyli dla n â‰¥ 2 iloraz &lt; 1.<br>
            <br>
            Dla n = 1: <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">1+1</span><span class="frac-den">2Â·1</span></span> = <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">2</span><span class="frac-den">2</span></span> = 1 â†’ a<sub>1</sub> = a<sub>2</sub> (nie roÅ›nie, nie maleje)
        </div>
        <div class="result">CiÄ…g nie jest monotoniczny w Å›cisÅ‚ym sensie: a<sub>1</sub> = a<sub>2</sub> = <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">1</span><span class="frac-den">2</span></span>, a od n = 2 maleje.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="example">
        <div class="example-header">
            <div class="icon">ğŸ”</div>
            PrzykÅ‚ad 10 â€” Wyznaczanie wzoru z opisu
        </div>
        <p>CiÄ…g skÅ‚ada siÄ™ z kolejnych wielokrotnoÅ›ci liczby 7, poczÄ…wszy od 7. Podaj wzÃ³r ogÃ³lny i zbadaj monotonicznoÅ›Ä‡.</p>
        <div class="step">
            <strong>Wyrazy:</strong> 7, 14, 21, 28, 35, â€¦<br>
            <strong>WzÃ³r:</strong> a<sub>n</sub> = 7n
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            <strong>MonotonicznoÅ›Ä‡:</strong><br>
            a<sub>n+1</sub> âˆ’ a<sub>n</sub> = 7(n+1) âˆ’ 7n = 7n + 7 âˆ’ 7n = 7 &gt; 0
        </div>
        <div class="result">CiÄ…g (a<sub>n</sub>) = (7n) jest rosnÄ…cy.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="example">
        <div class="example-header">
            <div class="icon">ğŸ”</div>
            PrzykÅ‚ad 11 â€” CiÄ…g rekurencyjny i monotonicznoÅ›Ä‡
        </div>
        <p>Dany jest ciÄ…g: <span class="im">a<sub>1</sub> = 10</span>, <span class="im">a<sub>n+1</sub> = a<sub>n</sub> / 2 + 1</span>. Wyznacz kilka wyrazÃ³w i okreÅ›l monotonicznoÅ›Ä‡.</p>
        <div class="step">
            a<sub>1</sub> = 10<br>
            a<sub>2</sub> = <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">10</span><span class="frac-den">2</span></span> + 1 = 6<br>
            a<sub>3</sub> = <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">6</span><span class="frac-den">2</span></span> + 1 = 4<br>
            a<sub>4</sub> = <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">4</span><span class="frac-den">2</span></span> + 1 = 3<br>
            a<sub>5</sub> = <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">3</span><span class="frac-den">2</span></span> + 1 = 2,5<br>
            a<sub>6</sub> = <span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">2,5</span><span class="frac-den">2</span></span> + 1 = 2,25
        </div>
        <div class="step">
            Zbadajmy formalnie: <br>
            a<sub>n+1</sub> âˆ’ a<sub>n</sub> = (<span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">a<sub>n</sub></span><span class="frac-den">2</span></span> + 1) âˆ’ a<sub>n</sub> = âˆ’<span class="frac im"><span class="frac-num">a<sub>n</sub></span><span class="frac-den">2</span></span> + 1 = 1 âˆ’ a<sub>n</sub>/2<br>
            <br>
            RÃ³Å¼nica &lt; 0 gdy a<sub>n</sub> &gt; 2. Z obliczeÅ„ widaÄ‡, Å¼e wszystkie wyrazy &gt; 2, wiÄ™c rÃ³Å¼nica jest ujemna.
        </div>
        <div class="result">CiÄ…g jest malejÄ…cy (wyrazy zbliÅ¼ajÄ… siÄ™ do 2).</div>
    </div>
</section>

<div class="separator"></div>

